{"title_page": "Ilkka Tuomisto", "text_new": "{{short description|Finnish Paralympic athlete}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name = Ilkka Tuomisto\n| nationality = Finnish\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|01|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[H\u00e4meenkyr\u00f6]], [[Finland]]\n| height = 1.77 m\n| weight = 65 kg\n| country = {{FIN}}\n| sport = [[Paralympic Nordic skiing]] ([[Paralympic cross-country skiing]] and [[Paralympic biathlon]])\n| disability_class = [[LW6/8]]\n| coach = [[Toni Myllyl\u00e4]]\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Men's [[para cross-country skiing]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{FIN}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Cross-country skiing at the Winter Paralympics|Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2014 Winter Paralympics|2014 Sochi]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2014 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 20 km Free|20km classic style standing]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|2010 Vancouver]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 km Sprint Classic|1km sprint classic standing]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2018 Winter Paralympics|2018 PyeongChang]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2018 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1.5 km sprint classical|1.5km sprint classic standing]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Ilkka Tuomisto''' (born 19 January 1984) is a Finnish male [[Paralympic cross-country skiing|Paralympic cross-country skier]] and [[Paralympic biathlon|biathlete]]. He has represented [[Finland at the Paralympics]] in [[2010 Winter Paralympics|2010]] and [[2014 Winter Paralympics|2014]] claiming two medals in his Paralympic career.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://ipc.infostradasports.com/asp/lib/theasp.asp?pageid=8937&sportid=-1&personid=919295|title=Ilkka Tuomisto|website=ipc.infostradasports.com|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/news/farm-focus-helps-ilkka-tuomisto-he-eyes-home-nordic-world-cup|title=Farm focus helps Ilkka Tuomisto as he eyes home Nordic World Cup|website=www.paralympic.org|language=en|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nTuomisto was born on 19 January 1984 with his left arm got amputated at his birth. He received his first prosthetic arm at the age of five. He took the sport of skiing at the age of 18.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\nTuomisto made his first appearance at the [[Winter Paralympics]] in 2010 and managed to claim a bronze medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 km Sprint Classic|men's 1 km Sprint Classic standing category]]. He was also the flagbearer for [[Finland at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]] during the opening ceremony of the multi-sport event.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.is.fi/maastohiihto/art-2000005502040.html|title=Karjatilan is\u00e4nt\u00e4 Ilkka Tuomisto jahtaa taas paralympiamitalia \u2013 \"En ole koskaan tehnyt numeroa k\u00e4den puuttumisesta\"|date=2017-12-25|work=Ilta-Sanomat|access-date=2018-02-07|language=fi-FI}}</ref>\n\nHe also took part in the [[2014 Winter Paralympics]] and clinched a silver medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2014 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 20 km Free|men's classic style standing category]].\n\nHe is qualified to compete at the [[2018 Winter Paralympics]] and took a bronze medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2018 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1.5 km sprint classical|men's 1.5 km Sprint Classic standing category]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.paralympic.org/news/ilkka-tuomisto-eyes-paralympic-success|title=Ilkka Tuomisto eyes Paralympic success|website=m.paralympic.org|language=en|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|id=ilkka-tuomisto|old_id=919295}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tuomisto, Ilkka}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish male cross-country skiers]]\n[[Category:Finnish male biathletes]]\n[[Category:Cross-country skiers at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Cross-country skiers at the 2014 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic cross-country skiers of Finland]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Finland]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for Finland]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2014 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:People from H\u00e4meenkyr\u00f6]]\n[[Category:Cross-country skiers at the 2018 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2018 Winter Paralympics]]\n\n\n{{Finland-wintersport-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Finnish Paralympic athlete}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name = Ilkka Tuomisto\n| nationality = Finnish\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|01|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[H\u00e4meenkyr\u00f6]], [[Finland]]\n| height = 1.77 m\n| weight = 65 kg\n| country = {{FIN}}\n| sport = [[Paralympic Nordic skiing]] ([[Paralympic cross-country skiing]] and [[Paralympic biathlon]])\n| disability_class = [[LW6/8]]\n| coach = [[Toni Myllyl\u00e4]]\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{FIN}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[cross-country skiing]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2014 Winter Paralympics|Sochi 2014]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2014 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 20 km Free|20km classic style standing]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2010 Winter Paralympics|Vancouver 2010]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 km Sprint Classic|1km sprint classic standing]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2018 Winter Paralympics|PyeongChang 2018]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2018 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1.5 km sprint classical|1.5km sprint classic standing]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Ilkka Tuomisto''' (born 19 January 1984) is a Finnish male [[Paralympic cross-country skiing|Paralympic cross-country skier]] and [[Paralympic biathlon|biathlete]]. He has represented [[Finland at the Paralympics]] in [[2010 Winter Paralympics|2010]] and [[2014 Winter Paralympics|2014]] claiming two medals in his Paralympic career.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://ipc.infostradasports.com/asp/lib/theasp.asp?pageid=8937&sportid=-1&personid=919295|title=Ilkka Tuomisto|website=ipc.infostradasports.com|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/news/farm-focus-helps-ilkka-tuomisto-he-eyes-home-nordic-world-cup|title=Farm focus helps Ilkka Tuomisto as he eyes home Nordic World Cup|website=www.paralympic.org|language=en|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nTuomisto was born on 19 January 1984 with his left arm got amputated at his birth. He received his first prosthetic arm at the age of five. He took the sport of skiing at the age of 18.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\nTuomisto made his first appearance at the [[Winter Paralympics]] in 2010 and managed to claim a bronze medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 km Sprint Classic|men's 1 km Sprint Classic standing category]]. He was also the flagbearer for [[Finland at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]] during the opening ceremony of the multi-sport event.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.is.fi/maastohiihto/art-2000005502040.html|title=Karjatilan is\u00e4nt\u00e4 Ilkka Tuomisto jahtaa taas paralympiamitalia \u2013 \"En ole koskaan tehnyt numeroa k\u00e4den puuttumisesta\"|date=2017-12-25|work=Ilta-Sanomat|access-date=2018-02-07|language=fi-FI}}</ref>\n\nHe also took part in the [[2014 Winter Paralympics]] and clinched a silver medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2014 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 20 km Free|men's classic style standing category]].\n\nHe is qualified to compete at the [[2018 Winter Paralympics]] and took a bronze medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2018 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1.5 km sprint classical|men's 1.5 km Sprint Classic standing category]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.paralympic.org/news/ilkka-tuomisto-eyes-paralympic-success|title=Ilkka Tuomisto eyes Paralympic success|website=m.paralympic.org|lan